      "prompt_template": {
        "description": "LLM提示词模板，用于帮助模型理解此配方类型 / LLM prompt template to help the model understand this recipe type",
        "template": "这是 Create 模组的粉碎轮配方类型。粉碎轮是一种强力的机械设备，用于粉碎矿石、石头等硬质材料。\n\n关键特征：\n- 只接受单个输入物品\n- 可以产生1-7个输出物品（主产物+多个副产物）\n- 支持概率输出（chance字段，0.0-1.0）\n- 处理时间默认100游戏刻，可根据材料硬度调整\n\n判断标准：\n1. 如果输入是矿石，优先考虑此类型（产出粉碎矿物+副产物）\n2. 如果涉及石头、砾石等硬质材料的粉碎，使用此类型\n3. 如果需要将方块破碎成更小的材料，此类型是最佳选择\n\n典型应用场景：\n- 铁矿石→粉碎铁（1个）+额外粉碎铁（2个，75%概率）+圆石（1个，12%概率）\n- 砾石→沙子（1个）+燧石（1个，25%概率）\n- 回收装备获得原材料\n\n输出格式说明：\n- results 是数组，第一个通常是主产物（chance可省略或为1.0）\n- 后续是副产物，需要指定chance概率\n- 副产物概率应该合理（常见：0.75, 0.5, 0.25, 0.12）\n\n注意事项：\n- 粉碎主要用于矿物和硬质材料，不适合食物或软质材料\n- 处理时间可根据材料硬度调整（矿石通常150，普通石头100）\n- 副产物数量不要过多（建议1-3个副产物）\n\nThis is the crushing wheel recipe type from Create mod. Crushing wheels are powerful mechanical devices for crushing ores, stones, and other hard materials.\n\nKey characteristics:\n- Accepts only a single input item\n- Can produce 1-7 output items (main product + multiple byproducts)\n- Supports probability outputs (chance field, 0.0-1.0)\n- Default processing time 100 ticks, adjustable based on material hardness\n\nJudgment criteria:\n1. If input is ore, prioritize this type (outputs crushed ore + byproducts)\n2. If involves crushing stone, gravel, or other hard materials, use this type\n3. If need to break blocks into smaller materials, this is the best choice\n\nTypical use cases:\n- Iron ore → crushed iron (×1) + extra crushed iron (×2, 75%) + cobblestone (×1, 12%)\n- Gravel → sand (×1) + flint (×1, 25%)\n- Recycle equipment to get raw materials\n\nOutput format:\n- results is an array, first item is usually main product (chance can be omitted or 1.0)\n- Following items are byproducts, need to specify chance\n- Byproduct chances should be reasonable (common: 0.75, 0.5, 0.25, 0.12)\n\nNotes:\n- Crushing is mainly for minerals and hard materials, not suitable for food or soft materials\n- Processing time can be adjusted based on hardness (ore usually 150, regular stone 100)\n- Don't use too many byproducts (recommend 1-3 byproducts)"
      },
