      "prompt_template": {
        "description": "LLM提示词模板，用于帮助模型理解此配方类型 / LLM prompt template to help the model understand this recipe type",
        "template": "这是 Create 模组的搅拌器配方类型。搅拌器用于混合多种材料，特别适合制作合金、化合物和混合物。\n\n关键特征：\n- 可以接受1-9种输入材料\n- 产生1-4个输出物品\n- 支持三种热量需求：none（无需加热）、heated（需要加热）、superheated（需要超级加热）\n- 适合制作合金、化合物等需要混合的材料\n\n判断标准：\n1. 如果需要混合2种以上材料制作合金（如黄铜=铜+锌），使用此类型\n2. 如果输出物品名称包含'合金'、'化合物'等关键词，强烈建议使用此类型\n3. 如果原配方涉及材料的均匀混合（而非简单堆叠），此类型是最佳选择\n\n热量需求说明：\n- none: 常温混合（如面团、简单混合物）\n- heated: 需要加热（如大多数合金，温度>100°C）\n- superheated: 需要超级加热（如高级合金，温度>300°C）\n\n典型应用场景：\n- 安山合金：安山岩+铁粒→安山合金（需要加热）\n- 黄铜：铜锭+锌锭→黄铜锭×2（需要加热）\n- 面团：面粉+水→面团（无需加热）\n\n注意事项：\n- 合金制作通常需要heated或superheated\n- 输出数量可能大于输入（如2种材料产出2-3个产物）\n- 区分搅拌(mixing)和粉碎(crushing)：搅拌是混合，粉碎是破碎\n- 区分搅拌和烹饪：搅拌用于非食物材料，烹饪用于食物\n\nThis is the mechanical mixer recipe type from Create mod. The mixer is used to combine multiple materials, especially suitable for making alloys, compounds, and mixtures.\n\nKey characteristics:\n- Can accept 1-9 input materials\n- Produces 1-4 output items\n- Supports three heat requirements: none (no heating), heated (heating required), superheated (super heating required)\n- Suitable for making alloys, compounds, and other materials requiring mixing\n\nJudgment criteria:\n1. If need to mix 2+ materials to make alloys (e.g., brass = copper + zinc), use this type\n2. If output name contains 'alloy', 'compound' keywords, strongly recommend this type\n3. If original recipe involves uniform mixing (not simple stacking), this is the best choice\n\nHeat requirement explanation:\n- none: Room temperature mixing (e.g., dough, simple mixtures)\n- heated: Heating required (most alloys, temp >100°C)\n- superheated: Super heating required (advanced alloys, temp >300°C)\n\nTypical use cases:\n- Andesite alloy: andesite + iron nugget → andesite alloy (heated)\n- Brass: copper ingot + zinc ingot → brass ingot ×2 (heated)\n- Dough: flour + water → dough (none)\n\nNotes:\n- Alloy making usually requires heated or superheated\n- Output count can be greater than input (e.g., 2 materials produce 2-3 products)\n- Distinguish mixing from crushing: mixing combines, crushing breaks\n- Distinguish mixing from cooking: mixing for non-food materials, cooking for food"
      },
